file.content:
//axhrb_regime
{rbrv_regime}

This regime specifies variables that define container vessel configurations within the Recipe Bottle system.
Each
{rbrv_regime}
instance represents a vessel image source: bound from an external registry, conjured from a Dockerfile, or grafted from a local build.
RBRV assignment files are found in `rbev-vessels/*/rbrv.env` and configure image sourcing for bottle deployments.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrv_sigil}

Unique identifier for the vessel.
Must be 1-64 characters forming a valid cross-context identifier.
Must match the vessel directory name.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrv_description}

Human-readable description of the vessel purpose.
Optional; 0-512 characters.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrv_user}

Runtime user for the vessel container.
Optional; 0-64 characters.
When set, declares the non-root user that downstream orchestration (compose user directive, SSH authentication, exec sessions) should target.
When unset, the container runs as its image default.
Applies across all vessel modes: conjure vessels create the user in their Dockerfile; bind and graft vessels declare a user that already exists in the image.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrv_vessel_mode}

Selects vessel provisioning strategy.
Must be
{rbrv_vessel_mode_bind},
{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure},
or
{rbrv_vessel_mode_graft}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_egress_mode}

Selects which worker pool the primary build operation uses.
Must be `tether` (public egress) or `airgap` (`NO_PUBLIC_EGRESS`).
Inscribe and enshrine always use tether regardless of this setting.
About and vouch always use airgap regardless of this setting.
Conjure and bind use the pool selected by this variable.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrv_group_binding}

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
{rbrv_vessel_mode_bind}

Variables in this group apply only when
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
is
{rbrv_vessel_mode_bind}.
Binding retrieves a pre-built image from an external registry without local build steps.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_bind_image}

Fully-qualified image reference to copy from an external registry.
Must be a valid FQIN; 1-512 characters.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_bind_optional_dockerfile}

Optional path to reference Dockerfile for the upstream image.
When configured, the Dockerfile content is passed to
{rbtgo_ark_about}
and embedded in the about artifact as `recipe.txt`.
Optional; 0-512 characters.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrv_group_conjuring}

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure}

Variables in this group apply only when
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
is
{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure}.
Conjuring builds a vessel image locally from a Dockerfile and build context in the repository.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_conjure_dockerfile}

Path to Dockerfile relative to repository root.
Must be 1-512 characters.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_conjure_bldcontext}

Build context path relative to repository root.
Must be 1-512 characters.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_conjure_platforms}

Space-separated list of target platforms for multi-platform builds.
Must be 1-512 characters.
Examples: `linux/amd64`, `linux/amd64 linux/arm64`.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrv_group_image}

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure}

Variables in this group declare base image dependencies for multi-stage Dockerfiles.
Up to 3 indexed slots (n = 1, 2, 3).
{rbtgo_ark_enshrine}
resolves each
{rbrv_image_origin}
to a GAR-mirrored
{rbrv_image_anchor}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_image_origin}

Upstream base image tag declaration (e.g., `python:3.11-slim`).
Vessel author declares intent; the {at_foundry} resolves to a concrete reference.
Optional; 0-512 characters per slot.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_image_anchor}

GAR-mirrored, content-addressed anchor for the base image.
Written by
{rbtgo_ark_enshrine}.
Format: `{sanitized-origin}-{10-char-sha256}`.
When present, conjure substitutes the full GAR reference.
When absent, conjure passes
{rbrv_image_origin}
through as the upstream tag.
Optional; 0-512 characters per slot.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrv_group_grafting}

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
{rbrv_vessel_mode_graft}

Variables in this group apply only when
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
is
{rbrv_vessel_mode_graft}.
Grafting accepts a locally-built image pushed to GAR via native docker/podman push.
No Cloud Build involvement for the image itself — about and vouch run in Cloud Build after push.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_graft_image}

Local image reference for graft operations.
Must be 1-512 characters.
Provides the image argument to
{rbtgo_ark_graft}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_graft_optional_dockerfile}

Optional path to Dockerfile used for the local build.
When configured, the Dockerfile content is passed to
{rbtgo_ark_about}
and embedded in the about artifact as `recipe.txt`.
Optional; 0-512 characters.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Sets defaults for all RBRV_ variables via `VAR="${VAR:-}"` pattern.
Detects unexpected RBRV_ variables via compgen prefix scan.
Builds ZRBRV_ROLLUP serialization string.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates fields via buv_env_* type checkers.
Checks mode-appropriate presence invariant: RBRV_BIND_IMAGE for bind, RBRV_CONJURE_DOCKERFILE for conjure, optional RBRV_GRAFT_IMAGE for graft.
Validates optional Dockerfile paths when configured: RBRV_BIND_OPTIONAL_DOCKERFILE (bind), RBRV_GRAFT_OPTIONAL_DOCKERFILE (graft).

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders via rbcr_* shared module.
Sections: Core Vessel Identity, Egress Mode, Binding Configuration, Conjuring Configuration, Grafting Configuration.
Displays unexpected variables in red.
Validates after full render completes.

//axhro_list
{rbkro_list}

Enumerates available vessel instances by scanning subdirectories of RBRR_VESSEL_DIR for rbrv.env files.
Returns sigil identifiers suitable for instance selection.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}

NOTE: This operation conjures an
{rbtga_ark_image}
in
{rbtgi_repository}
by building a container image from a vessel specification. The
{rbtr_director}
performs the build via
{gcb_service}
using direct `builds.create` API submission.

NOTE: Conjure produces both the image and about artifacts in a single Cloud Build job submitted via `builds.create`.
The about steps (`rbgja01`-`rbgja04`) are embedded via stitch alongside the build steps.
The vouch artifact is created by the subsequent {rbtgo_ark_vouch} pipeline stage (always a separate Cloud Build job).

NOTE: The
{rbtga_hallmark}
is minted locally by the
{rbtr_director}
before submission.
The Director knows the complete artifact tag set before the build begins -- naming authority and verification authority are the same entity.

NOTE: The conjure build job runs on the worker pool selected by the vessel's `RBRV_EGRESS_MODE`: tether pool for vessels needing public internet (e.g., `apt-get` in Dockerfile), airgap pool for vessels with all dependencies enshrined in GAR.
The subsequent {rbtgo_ark_vouch} always runs on the airgap pool regardless of vessel egress mode.

The conjure operation:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel contains conjuring configuration (RBRV_CONJURE_DOCKERFILE, RBRV_CONJURE_BLDCONTEXT)

//axhos_step
. *Registry Preflight*:
.. *Reliquary check*: HEAD request to `«RELIQUARY»/docker:latest` manifest in
{gar_service}.
{rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 — on 404, fail with directive to run inscribe first.
The reliquary is a co-versioned set of builder tool images inscribed from upstream into private GAR. Each vessel declares its reliquary; multiple datestamped reliquaries can coexist.
.. *Enshrine check*: For each indexed slot (n = 1, 2, 3) where both
{rbrv_image_origin}
and
{rbrv_image_anchor}
are set:
... Parse
{rbrv_image_anchor}
as a
{rbst_locator}
into package-path and tag
... HEAD request to `«LOCATOR-PATH»:«LOCATOR-TAG»` manifest in
{gar_service}
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 — on 404, fail with directive to run {rbtgo_ark_enshrine} first.
Multiple vessels sharing the same anchor need only one enshrine.
.. Preflight prevents wasted
{gcb_service}
submission time on missing images, with copy-paste remediation commands

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Base Images*:
.. For each indexed slot (n = 1, 2, 3) where
{rbrv_image_origin}
is set:
... If
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is present: parse the
{rbst_locator}
and resolve to full GAR image reference (`«GAR-REPO-BASE»/«LOCATOR-PATH»:«LOCATOR-TAG»`)
... If
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is absent: pass
{rbrv_image_origin}
through as the upstream tag (development path)
.. Resolved references become `RBF_IMAGE_n` build-args for the Dockerfile `ARG`/`FROM` pattern

//axhos_step
. *Assign Hallmark*:
.. Mint
{rbtga_hallmark}
locally on the Director's workstation
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK»` -- complete artifact tag set is now known before build submission

//axhos_step
. *Push Pouch*:
.. Package build context (Dockerfile and context files) as a FROM SCRATCH OCI image
.. Push to GAR tagged `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/pouch:«HALLMARK»`
.. {rbbc_require}
push succeeds -- the pouch delivers build context to
{gcb_service}

//axhos_step
. *Execute Build*:
.. Stitch
{rbtgr_build_json}
with all step image references and substitution variables
.. {rbbc_submit}
`POST «GCB_PROJECT_BUILDS_URL»` with Build resource JSON via `builds.create`
.. All build parameters in stitched
{rbtgr_build_json}
-- zero custom substitution overrides
.. Waits for build completion
.. On success, the
{rbtga_ark_image}
artifact is created with the
{rbtga_hallmark}
.. {rbtgr_provenance}
is auto-generated by Google as a signed attestation on the built image

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark_image}

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_hallmark}
The full
{rbtga_hallmark}
string.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_build_id}
The
{gcb_build}
job ID from the `builds.create` submission.
Used by
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
for
{rbtgr_provenance}
verification.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_gar_root}
{gar_service}
registry prefix.
Composable with
{rbf_fact_ark_stem}
for full artifact references.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_ark_stem}
Hallmark subtree prefix joining
{gar_service}
root with the hallmark path segment as `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»`.
Composable with basename and `:«HALLMARK»` tag for full artifact references.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_ark_yield}
Per-platform
{rbtga_ark_image}
reference.
One fact file per platform discovered during the build.

. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
vessel image built with hallmark tag

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates the
{rbtga_ark_image}
in
{rbtgi_repository}.
The {rbtr_director} retains `«BUILD_ID»` and `«HALLMARK»` from the conjure round-trip.
The `builds.create` job produces both the image and about artifacts under the hallmark subtree (about steps embedded via stitch).
{rbtgo_ark_ordain} chains only {rbtgo_ark_vouch} after the combined job completes, passing `«BUILD_ID»` for DSSE provenance verification.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_graft}

NOTE: This operation grafts a locally-built container image into
{rbtgi_repository}
via native docker/podman push.
No Cloud Build involvement in the image push — the image is already built on the local workstation.
No crane dependency — docker tag + docker push is sufficient for locally-present images.
No dirty-tree guard — git state is irrelevant to an already-built container.

NOTE: The name "graft" comes from botanical grafting — foreign material spliced onto rootstock.
The graft may take or may not.
The metaphor fits the trust posture: grafted images have no provenance chain and receive a GRAFTED verdict from
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}.

NOTE: Graft uses whatever container runtime the `docker` command resolves to in PATH, matching other {rbtr_director}-side operations.
No separate regime variable governs runtime selection for graft.

The
{rbtr_director}
grafts an image:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
local image reference provided as second argument (or defaulted from {rbrv_graft_image})
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel mode is {rbrv_vessel_mode_graft}

//axhos_step
. *Load Vessel Configuration*:
.. Source vessel configuration from `rbrv.env`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_SIGIL»` from {rbrv_sigil}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_MODE»` from {rbrv_vessel_mode}
.. {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_MODE»` is `graft`

//axhos_step
. *Verify Local Image Exists*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker image inspect «LOCAL_IMAGE_REF»` (or podman equivalent)
.. {rbbc_require}
image exists in local container runtime
.. {rbbc_store}
`«LOCAL_DIGEST»` from local image inspect
.. {rbbc_store}
`«LOCAL_PLATFORMS»` from local image manifest (typically single-platform for local builds)

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark*:
.. {rbbc_call}
query local container runtime for image creation timestamp via `docker image inspect` (the `Created` field — OCI Image Configuration spec, exposed at `.Created` by both docker and podman)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE_CREATED»` as the image's creation timestamp, converted to `YYMMDDHHMMSS` format
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PUSH_TIMESTAMP»` as current UTC time (`YYMMDDHHMMSS`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK»` as `g«IMAGE_CREATED»-r«PUSH_TIMESTAMP»`
.. T1 encodes when the image was created (a fact about the artifact); T2 encodes when it was pushed to GAR
.. NOTE: The `created` field may be `1970-01-01T00:00:00Z` for reproducible builds. This produces `g700101000000-r...` — a true statement about the image, not an error.

//axhos_step
. *Tag and Push Image*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker login` to GAR registry with director credentials
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_TAG»` as `«GAR_HOST»/«GAR_PATH»/{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/image:«HALLMARK»`
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker tag «LOCAL_IMAGE_REF» «REGISTRY_TAG»`
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker push «REGISTRY_TAG»`
.. {rbbc_require}
push succeeds

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark_image}

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_hallmark}
The full
{rbtga_hallmark}
string.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_build_id}
